cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.GR 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper deals with robust estimation for homography and fundamental matrix fitting, which are common problems in computer vision. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper introduces a new model quality function and a novel marginalization procedure, which are related to machine learning techniques. 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is a possible category as robust estimation is important in robotics applications. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper proposes a new sampler that exploits the structure of real-world data, which is related to artificial intelligence techniques. 
- cs.GR (Graphics) is a less likely category, but still possible as robust estimation is also important in computer graphics applications.
